    • Constructor Detail

      • FunctionFactory

        FunctionFactory(java.lang.String[] parameterNames,
                BigRational[] lowerBounds,
                BigRational[] upperBounds)
        Creates a new function factory. parameterNames, lowerBounds, upperBounds all must have the same length. Each index into these arrays represents respectively the name, lower and upper bound of a given variable. After this function factory has been created, the number of variables, their names and bounds are fixed and cannot be changed anymore.
        Parameters:
        parameterNames - names of parameters
        lowerBounds - lower bounds of parameters
        upperBounds - upper bounds of parameters
